The paper discusses conflict resolution in distributed systems, which is a common topic in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on data structures, specifically the Conflict-free Replicated Data Collection (CRDC), which falls under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of replicas and data centers suggests a connection to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of developing upper-layer applications, which is a topic in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a design framework, which falls under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
